{"success": true, "message": "Fetched question.", "data": {"showTimer": true, "showAttemptInsight": true, "playSounds": true, "dontShowCorrectAnswerImmediately": false, "_id": "6682bd04ba0e94a3c4025a01", "type": "singleCorrect", "level": 2, "category": null, "approximateTimeRequired": 90, "imageBaseUrl": null, "helperText": null, "source": "", "questionLabels": [], "question": {"text": "<p>Given below are the two statements: one is labeled as Assertion (A) and the other is labeled as Reason (R).</p><p>Assertion (A): There is a considerable increase in covalent radius from <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>N</mi></math> to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi></math>. However from <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi><mi>s</mi></math> to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>B</mi><mi>i</mi></math> only a small increase in covalent radius is observed.</p><p>Reason (R): covalent and ionic radii in a particular oxidation state increases down the group.</p><p>In the light of the above statement, choose the most appropriate answer from the options given below:</p>", "image": null}, "options": [{"id": "Dldxv", "text": "(A) is false but (R) is true", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "P4P0j", "text": "Both (A) and (R) are true but (R) is not the correct explanation of (A)", "image": null, "isCorrect": true}, {"id": "nxChT", "text": "(A) is true but (R) is false", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "p6IO8", "text": "Both (A) and (R) are true and (R) is the correct explanation of (A)", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}], "correctValue": null, "solution": {"text": "<p>There is a considerable increase in covalent radius from <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi></math> to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi></math>. However, from <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>As</mi></math>\u00a0to\u00a0<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>Bi</mi></math>\u00a0only a small increase in covalent radius is observed.\u00a0This is due to the presence of completely filled d and/or f orbitals in heavier members.</p><p>As going down in a group, the number of shells increases, hence the covalent and ionic radii increases.</p><p>Both (A) and (R) are true but (R) is not the correct explanation of (A)</p><p>But the correct explanation is the presence of completely\u00a0filled d and f-orbitals of heavier members.</p>", "image": null}, "videoSolution": null, "bucket": "Easy Ques (Board Level)", "concepts": [], "masterId": "MOGJMPYQ53615211", "subject": "Chemistry", "subjects": ["615d70bd9948bc1b21da2b1f"], "chapters": ["615d6fed2b295b085ab6ebac"], "topics": [], "previousYearPapers": [{"_id": "65c4c0c11d30997d3436bb02", "title": "JEE Main 2024 (30 Jan Shift 1)", "isVisible": true}], "numericalLowerLimit": null, "numericalUpperLimit": null, "classes": [], "microConcepts": [], "exams": ["615d76b2c52ffa3c944600df"], "isRemoved": false, "cpyqbSubjects": ["615f0cf69476412f48314dac", "616057040283de43c87e3e16", "61bb58281213731910ea0b71", "6160579d0283de43c87e3e1f", "61964f94a5a526011886801e", "61c055f6e8ce0dc8a5c62d34", "61a8a2cce8ce0dc8a5c62d2e", "6160577e0283de43c87e3e1c", "616057210283de43c87e3e19", "629105adee9e3ae00d63352c", "62962075e7f8e9ac4daeafd8", "629f385f263330a77be9fa7e", "629f39e4ac11b26562e0625c", "61964ff3a5a5260118868022", "64d50c263df7f4a7f3017f70", "66b79b89d4b564dfab4f94d0", "678ea9a09cc79e5f592bdc12", "67fa602f4468eb1307ceb0ae", "6807d350647479b8e869647a"], "cpyqbChapters": ["6160247b7b82dd1366035a18", "6160247cf3a1c434932a4a88", "6160247ab6649a28dbb20abf", "61bb822bb4fb582ae09d2bd9", "61964c9bd2cad6ca730c35eb", "61964c9b440022dde741c32c", "6160247be77fd39da8bbabec", "61602479b6bda5480d7f73bd", "61e7bd80be29bf9b0cc9a13e", "61c089bab09d88093a4a36a4", "629109db0f9ec90f29d91e43", "629f38feee42062b717eb566", "62962117279